{{Infobox journal | title = Differences | cover = Diffcover2013.jpg | editor = Elizabeth Weed, Ellen Rooney | discipline = [[Cultural studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Differences | publisher = [[Duke University Press]] | country = | frequency = Triannually | history = 1989 | openaccess = | license = | impact = 0.310 | impact-year = 2015 | website = http://differences.dukejournals.org/ | link1 = http://differences.dukejournals.org/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://differences.dukejournals.org/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | link3 = https://muse.jhu.edu/journal/47 | link3-name = Project MUSE archive (1998-2004) | JSTOR = | OCLC = 186382457 | LCCN = 89650873 | CODEN = DIFFEX | ISSN = 1040-7391 | eISSN = 1527-1986 }} '''''Differences: A Journal of Feminist Cultural Studies''''' (stylized "difference''s''") is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that was established in 1989 by [[Naomi Schor]] and Elizabeth Weed. It covers research in [[cultural studies]]. The current [[editors-in-chief]] are Elizabeth Weed and Ellen Rooney. The journal, though autonomous, is housed by the [[Pembroke Center for Teaching and Research on Women]] ([[Brown University]]). It was originally published by [[Indiana University Press]], but since 2003 (volume 14) it has been published by [[Duke University Press]].
